WEBVTT

00:00.960 --> 00:04.254
[YOSHINOBU]
Yaga, what is that thing?

00:04.672 --> 00:07.382
It is possible to have
man-made cursed corpses

00:07.424 --> 00:08.592
act more autonomously

00:08.634 --> 00:10.511
than other forms
of manipulation.

00:11.052 --> 00:13.764
But they're always powered by
consuming cursed energy

00:13.806 --> 00:15.182
from the sorcerer.

00:15.975 --> 00:18.268
And yet, that thing
is sustaining itself

00:18.310 --> 00:20.145
on its own cursed energy.

00:21.981 --> 00:24.650
The higher-ups are currently
trying to designate you

00:24.692 --> 00:25.985
as a special grade,

00:26.193 --> 00:28.863
and officially sentence you
to indefinite imprisonment.

00:29.738 --> 00:33.116
Because if you can intentionally
create a thing like that,

00:33.158 --> 00:34.326
then it stands to reason

00:34.368 --> 00:36.996
you could easily
create your own army.

00:37.872 --> 00:40.248
So tell me, Yaga.

00:41.500 --> 00:45.004
You truly have no idea of
how that thing was created?

00:45.044 --> 00:46.964
Is that your official stance?

00:47.006 --> 00:48.423
[water dripping]

00:49.675 --> 00:50.968
Yes.

00:51.802 --> 00:53.261
[TAKERU] Masamichi.

00:54.179 --> 00:56.015
Everyone's worried about you.

00:56.055 --> 00:57.975
They told me you seem down.

00:58.017 --> 00:59.226
[MASAMICHI] Did they?

01:00.101 --> 01:01.854
[insects trilling]

01:01.896 --> 01:03.522
[TAKERU]
So I told them all this.

01:03.856 --> 01:05.566
If Masamichi is feeling down,

01:05.607 --> 01:06.901
we just have to cheer him up.

01:09.361 --> 01:10.529
Is that so?

01:11.363 --> 01:14.073
- Pretty smart, huh?
- [chuckles] Pretty smart.

01:14.115 --> 01:15.576
[Takeru laughs]

01:15.617 --> 01:16.869
Takeru.

01:16.911 --> 01:19.454
I'm sorry, but I have
to leave home for a while.

01:19.830 --> 01:22.081
Would you please
let the others know for me?

01:22.123 --> 01:23.959
[TAKERU] Leaving for work again?

01:24.001 --> 01:26.921
That's right.
It'll be a long trip too.

01:26.962 --> 01:27.963
Don't worry.

01:28.005 --> 01:29.297
This forest is still under

01:29.339 --> 01:31.550
the constant protection
of Tengen.

01:31.592 --> 01:33.301
And your mother will come soon.

01:33.343 --> 01:35.054
She'll be glad to see you.

01:36.430 --> 01:38.724
You'll be all right without me.

01:38.766 --> 01:40.059
I'm sure of it.

01:42.770 --> 01:44.354
[TAKERU] Masamichi.

01:45.188 --> 01:47.816
It sure will be lonely
around here without you.

01:47.858 --> 01:51.820
[sword clangs, scrapes]

01:52.821 --> 01:55.156
Kusakabe, are you sure?

01:55.198 --> 01:58.117
[ATSUYA] Just don't go telling
anyone that I helped you.

01:58.159 --> 02:00.203
You were captured
to lure Yaga out.

02:00.245 --> 02:01.705
That's all you need to know.

02:02.414 --> 02:05.000
Besides,
I owe that man a favor.

02:05.042 --> 02:08.087
- [drips]
- Go on. Get.

02:09.755 --> 02:11.590
Are you really sure about this?

02:12.257 --> 02:14.342
This thing is not your nephew.

02:14.384 --> 02:17.012
It's just a vessel
with your nephew's information.

02:17.554 --> 02:19.890
Are you trying to tell me
that I can't live in the present

02:19.932 --> 02:21.642
if I stay hung up on the dead,

02:21.683 --> 02:23.518
forever living in the past?

02:24.478 --> 02:28.231
Well, my little sister can
no longer live in the past.

02:28.273 --> 02:29.942
She needs
to live in the present,

02:29.984 --> 02:31.526
meaning with Takeru.

02:35.489 --> 02:36.907
Masamichi.

02:36.949 --> 02:39.576
I think that lady is my mother,
isn't she?

02:40.201 --> 02:41.453
[MASAMICHI] That's right.

02:41.495 --> 02:43.371
Good job recognizing her.

02:43.413 --> 02:45.332
[Takeru giggles]

02:46.041 --> 02:48.293
Yeah, I had a feeling
that's who she was.

02:50.087 --> 02:51.839
I must be a genius.

02:54.967 --> 02:56.510
[thuds]

02:56.551 --> 02:59.178
[Atsuya's sister whimpering]

02:59.513 --> 03:03.142
[whimpering]

03:03.182 --> 03:04.518
[ATSUYA'S SISTER] Takeru!

03:04.559 --> 03:10.189
[crying]

03:10.231 --> 03:11.566
Sorry, but...

03:12.275 --> 03:13.652
Don't worry, I get it.

03:13.694 --> 03:14.945
You can't let anyone know

03:15.029 --> 03:17.823
that your fully autonomous
cursed corpses exist.

03:18.239 --> 03:20.034
So he can't live with her.

03:20.075 --> 03:21.284
I'm sorry.

03:21.326 --> 03:23.202
Why are you apologizing?

03:23.996 --> 03:26.205
Thank you, by the way.

03:26.915 --> 03:28.207
I mean it.

03:28.750 --> 03:30.127
Thank you.

03:32.671 --> 03:34.255
[ASSASSIN] Principal Yaga?

03:34.297 --> 03:37.051
Where do you think you're going
without any cursed corpses?

03:38.135 --> 03:39.803
I'm going to see my son.

03:39.845 --> 03:41.429
[ASSASSIN]
You've been sentenced to death,

03:41.471 --> 03:43.140
so I don't think so.

03:43.182 --> 03:45.224
But why not save your own life?

03:45.266 --> 03:47.186
They'll let you live
if you just tell them

03:47.226 --> 03:48.979
how you create
those fully autonomous,

03:49.021 --> 03:50.856
man-made cursed corpses.

03:51.439 --> 03:53.150
[MASAMICHI]
You all sure got suddenly brave

03:53.192 --> 03:55.027
the moment Satoru Gojo is gone.

03:55.485 --> 03:56.528
[assassin scoffs]

03:56.570 --> 03:58.822
[♪ electric guitar playing]

04:18.257 --> 04:20.010
[Masamichi groans]

04:20.635 --> 04:22.554
[breathing shakily]

04:25.390 --> 04:26.516
[ASSASSIN] Principal.

04:27.226 --> 04:30.562
You may leave now.
I'll handle the rest by myself.

04:30.604 --> 04:31.688
Understood.

04:32.731 --> 04:35.650
[MASAMICHI] First,
you use the body's information

04:35.692 --> 04:38.153
to reproduce
the soul's information.

04:38.195 --> 04:39.988
Then the soul's information

04:40.030 --> 04:43.242
is placed inside
the cursed corpse's core.

04:45.202 --> 04:47.412
- [Panda panting]
- But that's not enough.

04:47.454 --> 04:48.830
You have to place cores

04:48.872 --> 04:51.458
that house three
highly compatible souls

04:51.499 --> 04:53.418
into a single cursed corpse.

04:53.460 --> 04:55.462
Then force those souls

04:55.503 --> 04:57.881
to observe each other
at all times.

04:57.923 --> 04:59.716
Once you do that step,

04:59.758 --> 05:02.469
it finally allows
the souls to stabilize,

05:02.510 --> 05:04.512
so self-awareness can take root.

05:04.554 --> 05:06.598
Roughly three months
after that's born,

05:06.640 --> 05:09.308
it will begin supplying
its own cursed energy.

05:09.350 --> 05:11.352
Why talk now?

05:12.311 --> 05:15.565
Why are you sharing this
with us now?

05:15.607 --> 05:17.776
Why not tell us sooner?

05:18.193 --> 05:20.403
Why not try to live longer?

05:21.488 --> 05:24.491
Because it's... it's a curse,

05:24.532 --> 05:26.910
Principal Gakuganji.

05:26.952 --> 05:31.248
It's a curse that is handed down
from me to you.

05:34.209 --> 05:36.086
[gasps] Masamichi!

05:36.128 --> 05:39.131
[panting]

05:46.471 --> 05:48.682
[YOSHINOBU]
Why don't you fight me?

05:48.723 --> 05:51.350
I assume you hate me enough
to kill me.

05:51.392 --> 05:53.937
[PANDA] Pandas aren't
bound by things like that.

05:54.646 --> 05:57.607
Besides, you were never
on bad terms with Masamichi.

05:59.193 --> 06:01.236
To me, you're just
the random knife

06:01.278 --> 06:02.904
that happened to fall upon him.

06:04.739 --> 06:05.699
But still,

06:05.740 --> 06:07.868
just make sure
you remember this.

06:08.367 --> 06:12.289
Even pandas can cry.

06:12.956 --> 06:19.796
[crying]

06:20.214 --> 06:22.381
[♪ opening theme song playing]

06:54.413 --> 06:58.585
JUJUTSU KAISEN

07:50.262 --> 07:52.847
Kinji Hakari is currently
running a fight club

07:52.889 --> 07:55.600
in an old parking garage
in Tochigi Prefecture,

07:55.642 --> 07:57.394
where he also acts as bookie.

07:57.769 --> 07:58.895
[YUJI] A fight club?

07:59.354 --> 08:01.898
[TENGEN] They host fist fights
between sorcerers.

08:01.940 --> 08:04.025
And the spectators are?

08:04.067 --> 08:06.903
[TENGEN]
Generally non-sorcerers.

08:06.945 --> 08:09.323
[MEGUMI] That blatantly
violates the secrecy mandated

08:09.364 --> 08:11.574
in Article Eight
of the Jujutsu Code.

08:11.616 --> 08:15.120
There are probably curse users
among the participants as well.

08:15.162 --> 08:16.997
So above all, be careful.

08:17.038 --> 08:18.165
[Yuji gasps softly]

08:19.249 --> 08:20.499
[YUJI] Why are we changing?

08:21.376 --> 08:22.377
[MEGUMI] Hakari was expelled

08:22.419 --> 08:24.338
for clashing
with the upper brass.

08:24.379 --> 08:27.424
He's also actively
violating jujutsu regulations.

08:27.882 --> 08:30.177
If he finds out we're
with Jujutsu High, he might run.

08:30.760 --> 08:32.929
It's like we're cops
and he's the robber.

08:34.014 --> 08:36.808
Huh? We're on
Jujutsu High's side now?

08:36.850 --> 08:39.060
[Megumi sighs]
We're in a gray zone.

08:39.102 --> 08:41.604
But in Hakari's eyes,
at least, yeah.

08:41.646 --> 08:43.982
[YUJI] Is he even likely
to cooperate with us?

08:44.024 --> 08:45.233
[MEGUMI] I'm not sure.

08:45.275 --> 08:47.568
All our teachers say
he's a good-for-nothing.

08:49.863 --> 08:51.114
But Okkotsu claimed

08:51.198 --> 08:53.450
Hakari has the potential
to be stronger than him.

08:53.492 --> 08:55.202
We definitely want his strength.

08:55.618 --> 08:57.454
[SHRIMP]
You brats better get on home.

08:57.496 --> 08:59.747
This is no place for you guys
to be hanging out.

08:59.789 --> 09:02.250
[MACHO] You have until the count
of three to turn around.

09:02.292 --> 09:04.669
After that,
I start swinging my fists.

09:05.295 --> 09:06.629
We need money.

09:06.796 --> 09:08.923
Let us join your little
fight club so we can earn some.

09:08.965 --> 09:10.425
[Macho grunts]

09:11.550 --> 09:13.428
[MACHO]
The first rule of our fight club

09:13.970 --> 09:16.890
is that you do not
talk about our fight club.

09:17.474 --> 09:19.767
Who blabbed?
And where can I find him?

09:19.809 --> 09:21.936
If I like what you say,
I won't beat you up.

09:21.978 --> 09:24.481
I never learned his name.
I killed him.

09:25.648 --> 09:27.108
It was about a month ago.

09:27.150 --> 09:29.528
Just some scumbag
who was all talk.

09:29.568 --> 09:32.030
[SHRIMP] Kondo
disappeared about a month ago.

09:33.365 --> 09:35.492
- [MEGUMI] I can take his slot.
- [cell phone ringing]

09:35.534 --> 09:37.702
Or if you prefer,
I can just beat you to a pulp

09:37.744 --> 09:38.953
in front of your boss.

09:38.995 --> 09:39.996
[YUJI] Oh, yeah.

09:40.247 --> 09:42.416
He'd be wary if we
suddenly asked to see him.

09:42.457 --> 09:44.876
I guess we shouldn't know
his name's Hakari, either.

09:44.918 --> 09:46.669
Time to zip the lips.

09:46.711 --> 09:47.837
[SHRIMP] Are you sure?

09:48.755 --> 09:50.006
That's enough!

09:50.048 --> 09:52.050
The boss is giving you
the go-ahead.

09:52.591 --> 09:55.429
You're lucky one of our fighters
just dropped out.

09:55.470 --> 09:56.555
One thing, though.

09:56.595 --> 09:58.597
Your friend's the one
who's fighting.

09:59.640 --> 10:02.018
- [YUJI] Hm?
- [MEGUMI] That's good for us.

10:02.060 --> 10:04.645
Itadori's better suited
for this kind of thing.

10:04.687 --> 10:06.647
No chance. I fight.

10:06.689 --> 10:09.025
[SHRIMP] The boss said
he doesn't like you.

10:09.067 --> 10:12.529
And if you don't like it,
then the deal's off.

10:13.029 --> 10:15.365
If that's the case, he'll fight.

10:15.407 --> 10:16.824
Fushiguro, that was risky.

10:16.866 --> 10:18.868
Your bluffs go
too far sometimes.

10:19.536 --> 10:20.745
[MEGUMI] You worry too much.

10:21.246 --> 10:24.124
If curse users are participating
in the fight club too,

10:24.165 --> 10:25.959
that means there must be
decent turnover.

10:26.000 --> 10:28.044
[YUJI] The curse users
are here, all right.

10:28.669 --> 10:31.256
If he was watching us
through security cameras,

10:32.048 --> 10:34.926
then there's a high chance
Hakari is in there as well.

10:34.968 --> 10:37.429
You snoop around
from the inside, Itadori.

10:37.804 --> 10:40.432
In the meantime, I'm gonna
check out that parking lot.

10:40.932 --> 10:42.725
- Maybe.
- [YUJI] Maybe?

10:42.767 --> 10:44.603
[MEGUMI]
He's ignoring me for now.

10:44.643 --> 10:47.147
If Hakari learns we're trying
to infiltrate his club,

10:47.188 --> 10:48.689
we'll lose his trust
and our opportunity

10:48.731 --> 10:50.024
to make contact with him.

10:50.442 --> 10:53.528
[YUJI] Well, we'll just resort
to force if that happens.

10:53.570 --> 10:56.281
That really should be
our last resort.

10:56.323 --> 10:57.698
We're here for one thing,

10:57.740 --> 11:00.785
to ask Hakari for
his cooperation in joining us.

11:00.827 --> 11:03.662
I'd like to avoid
harming any future alliances.

11:04.414 --> 11:05.582
To be honest,

11:05.790 --> 11:07.834
I don't think I should be
doing anything tonight.

11:07.875 --> 11:09.586
But I don't wanna waste
the time we do have

11:09.628 --> 11:11.546
until Tsumiki
is forced to participate

11:11.588 --> 11:12.713
in the culling game.

11:13.632 --> 11:16.593
Right now,
it's 5:00 p.m. on the tenth.

11:16.968 --> 11:18.719
So nine days until the deadline.

11:18.761 --> 11:20.347
I guess it took us longer
to get here

11:20.388 --> 11:22.223
than we originally
thought it would.

11:22.765 --> 11:25.226
[MEGUMI] That's why I'll be
looking for Hakari tonight.

11:26.353 --> 11:28.605
But if it looks too risky,
I'll pull out.

11:28.980 --> 11:30.398
That's why I said maybe.

11:30.607 --> 11:31.650
Got it.

11:33.443 --> 11:35.028
[MACHO]
There are only two rules.

11:35.069 --> 11:38.031
No running away,
and no using curse techniques.

11:38.072 --> 11:40.950
How come? I don't mind if
they're using curse techniques.

11:40.992 --> 11:42.035
It won't help 'em.

11:42.369 --> 11:43.911
[MACHO] Because most
of the crowd are non-sorcerers

11:43.953 --> 11:45.205
and can't see them.

11:45.913 --> 11:48.249
A fight no one can see sucks.

11:48.291 --> 11:49.917
And the "no running" rule?

11:50.335 --> 11:52.962
[MACHO] It means you fight where
the spectators can see you.

11:53.588 --> 11:55.714
[YUJI] It's all about
the spectators, huh?

11:55.756 --> 11:58.259
They paid to get in.
Business 101.

11:58.926 --> 12:00.387
So what's the boss like?

12:01.388 --> 12:02.721
Curious, huh?

12:03.431 --> 12:04.891
Well, yeah.

12:05.433 --> 12:06.767
[MACHO]
You'll know if you meet him.

12:06.809 --> 12:08.769
[YUJI] If, or when?

12:08.811 --> 12:10.605
[MACHO] There are
two kinds of matches.

12:10.647 --> 12:12.815
Real beat-downs
like today's tournament,

12:12.857 --> 12:14.359
and fixed bouts.

12:14.401 --> 12:16.403
The boss writes
the script for those.

12:17.987 --> 12:21.241
He might call for you if
you manage to shine out there.

12:21.740 --> 12:22.950
You're saying, to meet the boss,

12:22.992 --> 12:24.827
I just need to
put on a good show?

12:25.161 --> 12:27.746
You really can't make things
much simpler than that.

12:36.755 --> 12:38.091
[MACHO] Over there,

12:38.132 --> 12:39.926
that's your opponent for today.

12:41.969 --> 12:43.388
- [gasps]
- I was blown away

12:43.430 --> 12:45.223
the first time I saw him, too.

12:45.265 --> 12:46.349
Yeah.

12:47.100 --> 12:50.186
It really is all about
drawing in the crowd.

12:52.105 --> 12:53.814
Are you ready to get it started?

12:53.856 --> 12:57.068
Because it's time for the
Gachinko Fight Club Tournament!

12:57.527 --> 12:58.777
Hello, everybody!

12:58.819 --> 13:01.322
I'm your commentator
for the night, John Bobby!

13:01.364 --> 13:03.991
Allow me to introduce
tonight's exciting matchup!

13:04.033 --> 13:05.993
We're joined by
a sudden upstart.

13:06.035 --> 13:08.496
Will he rise up or burn out?

13:08.538 --> 13:10.831
It's the dangerous fireball kid,

13:10.873 --> 13:14.419
- Yuji Itadori!
- [crowd cheering]

13:14.461 --> 13:16.254
[JOHN] His opponent
stands like a panda,

13:16.296 --> 13:17.422
sits like a panda,

13:17.464 --> 13:18.923
and walks like a panda!

13:18.965 --> 13:21.718
Please welcome Panda!

13:21.968 --> 13:24.512
Now, place your bets!
Place your bets!

13:24.554 --> 13:26.889
Everyone ready to rumble?!

13:26.931 --> 13:29.768
[HAKARI] I can feel
my passion draining away.

13:30.310 --> 13:32.646
What's wrong, my sweet baby?

13:32.687 --> 13:35.982
If one is lucky,
then he's meant to be tested.

13:36.023 --> 13:37.358
It's boring to gamble

13:37.400 --> 13:39.611
when you know who'll win
from the start.

13:39.653 --> 13:41.279
There aren't
many stray sorcerers

13:41.321 --> 13:43.448
who are tough enough
to beat Panda.

13:43.490 --> 13:45.325
[JOHN] Whoa!

13:45.366 --> 13:47.201
[KIRARA] Looks like
you might be wrong.

13:47.243 --> 13:48.328
[HAKARI] Huh?

13:48.536 --> 13:50.789
FIGHTING ARENA
2ND FLOOR CH 6

13:50.829 --> 13:52.831
[♪ exciting music playing]

13:52.873 --> 13:54.959
[YUJI] Panda,
have you seen Hakari yet?

13:56.127 --> 13:57.295
No.

13:57.462 --> 13:58.505
TAP

13:59.088 --> 14:01.466
[roaring]

14:01.508 --> 14:03.760
He's not suspicious of me
'cause we know each other,

14:03.802 --> 14:05.512
but he's avoiding me.

14:06.095 --> 14:07.263
TAP TAP TAP TAP

14:07.305 --> 14:10.391
ROOOAR

14:11.017 --> 14:12.977
Meanwhile,
the other third-year's technique

14:13.019 --> 14:14.813
is also going to be a problem.

14:18.107 --> 14:19.693
[crowd cheering]

14:23.279 --> 14:25.031
[PANDA] I hope
you're hiding the fact

14:25.072 --> 14:26.700
that you're from Jujutsu High!

14:26.741 --> 14:28.660
[YUJI] Of course! [gasps]

14:28.702 --> 14:31.329
[PANDA] Good.
You know what to do now, right?

14:33.247 --> 14:34.749
[groans]

14:37.627 --> 14:38.712
Whoa!

14:38.753 --> 14:40.380
This is definitely the best bout

14:40.421 --> 14:42.757
in my career as a commentator!

14:42.799 --> 14:45.719
Even if I have only been one
for the last two weeks!

14:46.260 --> 14:47.303
Huh?

14:50.557 --> 14:51.599
TAP

14:53.309 --> 14:54.352
TAP

14:55.687 --> 14:56.730
TAP

14:57.355 --> 15:02.485
[yelling]

15:04.320 --> 15:05.405
TAP

15:05.446 --> 15:07.657
[Panda yelling]

15:07.699 --> 15:09.367
[groans]

15:09.868 --> 15:10.909
[groans]

15:11.202 --> 15:14.205
[JOHN] The winner, Itadori!

15:14.247 --> 15:15.456
[crowd cheering]

15:15.498 --> 15:16.583
Hey!

15:16.624 --> 15:18.668
That punch was a foul!

15:18.710 --> 15:22.756
Wait, I know.
I'm gonna call the SPCA on you!

15:23.339 --> 15:24.507
[YUJI] Your acting sucks.

15:24.549 --> 15:26.300
[HAKARI]
Send Itadori up to the roof

15:26.342 --> 15:28.010
after he wins the tournament.

15:28.052 --> 15:30.179
- [MACHO] Huh?
- [HAKARI] He's sure to win it.

15:30.221 --> 15:32.724
Plus, he's intentionally
fighting in three dimensions

15:32.766 --> 15:35.476
to wow the spectators
in the upper rafters.

15:35.518 --> 15:37.729
I can write a good script
with him.

15:37.771 --> 15:39.063
And like I always say...

15:40.398 --> 15:43.109
you have to strike
while the iron is hot!

15:43.942 --> 15:46.195
I've asked you to use a coaster
a hundred times.

15:46.237 --> 15:48.155
[MACHO] Got it.
And what about his buddy,

15:48.197 --> 15:49.908
the other brat who didn't fight?

15:49.948 --> 15:52.076
Continue to keep
a close eye on him.

15:52.118 --> 15:54.203
I'll send Kirara later
as backup.

15:54.245 --> 15:55.329
Huh?

15:55.371 --> 15:57.123
I'm feeling a buzz right now

15:57.164 --> 15:59.417
that I haven't felt
in a long time.

15:59.459 --> 16:00.959
I haven't felt this alive

16:01.001 --> 16:03.170
since my ex maxed out
my credit cards.

16:03.212 --> 16:05.840
I've asked you a million times
not to mention your ex.

16:05.882 --> 16:06.965
KINJI HAKARI
KIRARA HOSHI

16:08.551 --> 16:09.928
Things are looking good.

16:09.968 --> 16:13.389
It won't be too long before
Itadori and Hakari meet.

16:13.431 --> 16:14.515
[MEGUMI] Tell me, Panda,

16:14.973 --> 16:17.310
why haven't you been able
to see Hakari yet?

16:17.351 --> 16:20.354
Hm. Well, I do know
where he likes to stay.

16:20.396 --> 16:22.565
In the monitor room on the roof.

16:22.607 --> 16:24.943
But I haven't been able
to get close enough.

16:25.568 --> 16:26.861
Wait, why not?

16:26.903 --> 16:28.237
Even when I approached the door,

16:28.279 --> 16:30.156
I can't seem to
close the distance.

16:30.197 --> 16:33.618
The sensation feels similar
to Satoru's technique.

16:33.660 --> 16:36.788
It's probably
due to Kirara's technique.

16:36.830 --> 16:38.122
Kirara?

16:38.205 --> 16:40.875
But I thought the other
third-year student is a guy.

16:40.917 --> 16:42.042
Yeah, so what?

16:42.084 --> 16:43.085
So this.

16:43.127 --> 16:44.462
Does that phenomenon only occur

16:44.504 --> 16:46.673
when Kirara's
in the monitor room?

16:46.714 --> 16:47.841
I'm not sure.

16:48.132 --> 16:50.343
I've been focusing too much
on being a circus panda

16:50.384 --> 16:52.553
instead of pushing more
and making them run off.

16:52.595 --> 16:55.013
I'm just really glad
the two of you showed up.

16:55.473 --> 16:58.100
Do you think Itadori has
a chance to persuade him?

16:58.142 --> 16:59.560
It'll be tough.

16:59.602 --> 17:02.020
But it's just a matter of time
before he does.

17:02.062 --> 17:04.357
I think Itadori's light,
charming personality

17:04.398 --> 17:06.484
is a good match for
someone like Hakari.

17:06.526 --> 17:08.903
But you won't believe
how bad his acting sucks.

17:08.945 --> 17:10.947
[MEGUMI]
He doesn't just suck at it,

17:10.989 --> 17:13.324
he struggles
to even see lying as an option.

17:13.366 --> 17:14.492
Well, that explains it.

17:14.534 --> 17:16.369
But it didn't stop him
from talking trash

17:16.410 --> 17:17.704
about my acting.

17:17.745 --> 17:20.414
Anyway, once Itadori enters
the monitor room,

17:20.456 --> 17:22.750
I'll buy him time
by taking control of the place.

17:22.792 --> 17:24.168
[Megumi gasps] Are you sure?

17:24.210 --> 17:25.503
[PANDA] Don't worry about it.

17:25.545 --> 17:26.587
Everything will be fine.

17:26.963 --> 17:29.590
I know where all the cameras
and their blind spots are.

17:29.632 --> 17:31.175
How many guards are in there?

17:31.217 --> 17:32.510
Four at the entrance

17:32.552 --> 17:35.137
and two on each floor
except for up on the roof.

17:37.348 --> 17:39.017
Okay, we can handle that.

17:39.851 --> 17:42.311
The only real concern
is Kirara's technique.

17:42.353 --> 17:44.313
[PANDA] We can't do
anything about that now.

17:44.355 --> 17:47.984
If they can warp Itadori
out of there or warp in backup,

17:48.026 --> 17:50.028
we'll give up
on pursuing Hakari.

17:51.069 --> 17:52.697
Wow, you look so young.

17:52.739 --> 17:54.782
Are you still a first-year,
Yu-ie?

17:54.824 --> 17:55.992
Yu-ie?

17:56.200 --> 17:58.244
[KIRARA] Kin had to repeat
a year in middle school.

17:58.536 --> 18:00.454
[YUJI] Looks like
you have a happy life here.

18:00.496 --> 18:02.582
[Kirara laughs] Well, yeah.

18:02.623 --> 18:04.876
It's been a while
since Kin's gotten

18:04.918 --> 18:06.753
all heated up like this, though.

18:07.211 --> 18:11.716
You see, I simply love it
when Kin is passionate.

18:12.926 --> 18:14.343
[door shuts]

18:16.345 --> 18:17.597
[HAKARI] Itadori.

18:17.638 --> 18:19.807
Would you believe me if I said

18:19.849 --> 18:21.559
you can earn
a million yen a month

18:21.601 --> 18:24.520
by doing something that
takes only an hour a day to do?

18:25.563 --> 18:29.025
[YUJI] Well, I guess it depends
on what that something is.

18:29.859 --> 18:32.278
But you'll have to pay me
200,000 yen

18:32.319 --> 18:34.906
to buy the information
on what that something is.

18:34.948 --> 18:36.323
Huh?

18:36.365 --> 18:38.367
In that case,
I don't believe you.

18:38.409 --> 18:40.620
Good. Because just
like you suspected,

18:40.661 --> 18:43.205
I was presenting you
with a classic con.

18:43.247 --> 18:44.999
The swindler
pretends to be rich,

18:45.041 --> 18:46.333
selling the means to be rich

18:46.375 --> 18:48.920
to those desperate
to be rich in a classic scam,

18:48.962 --> 18:51.338
It's obvious if you
think about it logically,

18:51.380 --> 18:54.300
but there's a huge number
of fools who fall for it.

18:54.341 --> 18:55.593
And you know why?

18:55.635 --> 18:58.096
'Cause it all
has to do with passion.

18:58.136 --> 18:59.137
Passion?

18:59.430 --> 19:02.182
Both swindler and swindled
have the same passion.

19:02.224 --> 19:04.142
They both have
a compulsive drive

19:04.184 --> 19:06.020
to change their lives
for the better.

19:06.687 --> 19:10.066
People high on passion
lose sight of their judgment.

19:10.108 --> 19:12.150
Yet without passion,
no one in the world

19:12.192 --> 19:13.903
would ever fall in love.

19:13.945 --> 19:16.614
I love that obsessive passion.

19:17.239 --> 19:21.035
Do you know the most direct way
people deal with passion?

19:21.828 --> 19:23.329
Gambling?

19:23.370 --> 19:25.205
[laughs]

19:26.290 --> 19:29.085
First time I saw you,
I knew you would get it.

19:29.585 --> 19:31.838
After all, life is a gamble.

19:31.879 --> 19:34.340
I can't tell you the number
of women that have dumped me

19:34.381 --> 19:35.675
because they hate gambling.

19:35.800 --> 19:38.260
But I think they're the ones
who've got it all wrong.

19:38.803 --> 19:41.555
Our society throws out
those who can't bet big,

19:41.597 --> 19:43.683
as well as those who don't know
when to fold their hands

19:43.724 --> 19:45.059
and call it a night.

19:45.183 --> 19:48.312
There isn't a single person
alive who doesn't gamble.

19:48.354 --> 19:50.356
What people hate
isn't the gambling.

19:50.397 --> 19:53.317
It's the losing
and the being ruined forever.

19:54.276 --> 19:55.486
There must be some people

19:55.528 --> 19:57.571
who just wanna
live a peaceful life.

19:57.613 --> 20:00.282
Not anyone that I've ever met.

20:00.324 --> 20:03.577
All the people that I know
love passion above all.

20:03.619 --> 20:07.790
Passion equals gambling,
and gambling equals life.

20:07.832 --> 20:10.292
And love equals control.

20:10.334 --> 20:12.962
And I wanna control
this nation's passion

20:13.004 --> 20:14.839
through my fight club one day.

20:15.548 --> 20:17.967
With the existence
of curses going public

20:18.009 --> 20:19.844
and headquarters
barely able to function,

20:19.886 --> 20:22.555
this is my chance
to expand the business.

20:22.596 --> 20:24.849
I'm going to crush
the opposition,

20:24.891 --> 20:27.601
and I'll make them
publicly recognize my fight club

20:27.643 --> 20:31.064
in the coming revisions
to the jujutsu regulations.

20:31.105 --> 20:32.773
And to do that,

20:32.815 --> 20:34.984
I'll need a strong player
on my team.

20:36.443 --> 20:37.695
Itadori,

20:38.487 --> 20:41.741
how do you feel about
getting high on my passion?

20:42.867 --> 20:43.951
Look, boss,

20:44.118 --> 20:46.244
- I need to tell you--
- [cell phone ringing]

20:57.590 --> 21:00.051
I'm sorry,
I haven't offered you a drink.

21:00.093 --> 21:02.929
[YUJI] I'm good with anything
really, other than liquor.

21:02.970 --> 21:05.305
[HAKARI] What?
Can't handle it or something?

21:05.347 --> 21:08.059
[YUJI] No.
It's just, I'm still underage.

21:08.101 --> 21:10.603
You don't strike me as
the type to care about that.

21:10.644 --> 21:13.647
Did you know Gojo
can't hold his liquor either?

21:13.689 --> 21:15.315
Yeah? Who's Gojo?

21:16.192 --> 21:18.736
And I never said that I can't,
just that I haven't.

21:18.778 --> 21:20.780
- So why the act?
- Huh?

21:20.821 --> 21:22.740
[cell phone continues ringing]

21:28.704 --> 21:32.208
There isn't a single sorcerer
who hasn't heard of Satoru Gojo.

21:32.250 --> 21:34.127
So why did you feign ignorance?

21:34.168 --> 21:35.293
Were you...

21:36.545 --> 21:38.714
[gulping]

21:41.467 --> 21:43.928
- [slams]
- ...sent by Jujutsu High?

21:49.976 --> 21:52.352
- L-Listen. [yelps]
- [glass shatters]

21:52.394 --> 21:53.562
Hey! Hey!

21:53.604 --> 21:55.273
[Yuji groans]

21:55.815 --> 21:58.567
When I get a call
from Kirara's phone,

21:58.609 --> 22:00.820
it's a signal
something's fishy.

22:01.737 --> 22:02.738
[grunts]

22:03.114 --> 22:05.158
- Listen!
- Save it, kid!

22:05.199 --> 22:06.826
My passion has gone cold!

22:06.867 --> 22:09.829
EPISODE 52 PASSION

22:10.288 --> 22:12.456
[♪ closing theme song playing]

23:40.586 --> 23:42.629
[MEGUMI] If we can convince
them, negotiations with Hakari

23:42.671 --> 23:43.964
will go more smoothly.

23:44.006 --> 23:45.925
- [PANDA] Wait, Kirara!
- [YUJI] Stay out of this.

23:45.966 --> 23:48.928
[HAKARI] You have to show me!
Right here and now!

23:48.969 --> 23:50.679
[MEGUMI] Wait.
There's no time to waste.

23:50.721 --> 23:52.681
[KIRARA] Kin! He's in danger!

23:52.723 --> 23:54.934
NEXT EPISODE
COG
